column5: Anybody launch out of Bronte lately? Still on the west side where it always was or did it get moved with all the new development? Cost? Thanks in advance, kwikfish.
Bronte launch is in the same spot as always. West side of rivermouth. I think it's $15 or $17. I don't look I just plug in the credit card and print a ticket.
Ouch...  I have 2 nice free public launches within 5-10 minutes of my house...  $15-$17... That would add up considering I launch 2-4 times a week....
Must be nice. A few launches on the north shore of Erie are $20.
That's why I love Crystal Beach $5
PC ramp is free after the GSOD is over no?  I know it's free before the derby.
Port Credit was free last weekend!
